    </div>
    <div class="direction-wrap-layout1">
      <div class="section-heading heading-dark">
        <div class="item-title">
          <h2 class="item-heading">Eggs Benedict: Directions</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="step--1" class="row direction-st">
        <div class="col-lg-1" />
        <div class="col-lg-2">
          <div class="serial-number">&#13; Step 1 </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-9">
          <div class="direction-box-layout1">
            <div class="item-content">
              <p>Finely dice the onion and cut the bacon into medium-thick slices.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="item-figure mobile_hide"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item-figure mobile_show"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="step--2" class="row direction-st">
        <div class="col-lg-1" />
        <div class="col-lg-2">
          <div class="serial-number">&#13; Step 2 </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-9">
          <div class="direction-box-layout1">
            <div class="item-content">
              <p>Bring a deep saucepan of water to a rolling boil, lower the heat and pour in the vinegar. Swirl the water with a spoon to create a vortex. Carefully break one egg and slide it into the vortex. Stir the simmering water a little bit and boil the egg for 2 or 3 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, carefully remove the poached egg from the water and place it onto a paper towel to dry. Repeat the process with the second egg.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="item-figure mobile_hide"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item-figure mobile_show"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="step--3" class="row direction-st">
        <div class="col-lg-1" />
        <div class="col-lg-2">
          <div class="serial-number">&#13; Step 3 </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-9">
          <div class="direction-box-layout1">
            <div class="item-content">
              <p>Melt the butter in a frying pan and toast the slices of bread in it. Fry up the bacon and diced onion.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="item-figure mobile_hide"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item-figure mobile_show"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="step--4" class="row direction-st">
        <div class="col-lg-1" />
        <div class="col-lg-2">
          <div class="serial-number">&#13; Step 4 </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-9">
          <div class="direction-box-layout1">
            <div class="item-content">
              <p>Make the hollandaise. Make a double boiler by heating up a large pot of water and placing a smaller pot inside, so that the bottom doesnâ€™t touch the surface of the water. Melt the butter in the double boiler, whisk it and salt to taste. In a separate dish, whisk the egg and carefully dribble it into the hot butter. Whisk the mixture and add in the lemon juice.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="item-figure mobile_hide"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item-figure mobile_show"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="step--5" class="row direction-st">
        <div class="col-lg-1" />
        <div class="col-lg-2">
          <div class="serial-number">&#13; Step 5 </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-9">
          <div class="direction-box-layout1">
            <div class="item-content">
              <p>Assemble the dish: top the toasted bread with the fried bacon and onions, place a poached egg on top and pour over the hollandaise.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="item-figure mobile_hide"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item-figure mobile_show"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-paragraph">Cooking is easy!</div>
    </div>
